<!-- XOR CALLOUT -->
<div class=3D"xor" style=3D"margin-top:28px">
  <div class=3D"xor-inner">
    <div style=3D"font-size:28px;padding-top:2px"></div>
    <div>
      <div class=3D"xor-head">XOR Constraint - receiver_account_id vs benef=
iciary_id</div>
      <p class=3D"xor-body">
        Every transaction row has <strong>exactly one</strong> of these two=
 nullable FK columns set - never both, never neither.
        The one that's populated tells you whether money moved <em>inside</=
em> or <em>outside</em> the bank.
      </p>
      <div class=3D"code" style=3D"margin-top:10px;white-space:pre-wrap;ove=
rflow-x:hidden">CHECK (
  (receiver_account_id IS NULL) &lt;&gt; (beneficiary_id IS NULL)
)</div>
      <div class=3D"xor-cases">
        <div class=3D"xcase">
          <div class=3D"xcase-title" style=3D"color:var(--acc)">Internal Tr=
ansfer (40% of rows)</div>
          <span class=3D"set">receiver_account_id =3D "A4521"</span><br>
          <span class=3D"nil">beneficiary_id&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=
nbsp;=3D NULL</span><br><br>
          Money stays inside the bank.<br>
          Join accounts -&gt; get full receiver profile.<br>
          Then join customers -&gt; age, tenure, risk.
        </div>
        <div class=3D"xcase">
          <div class=3D"xcase-title" style=3D"color:var(--bene)">External T=
ransfer (60% of rows)</div>
          <span class=3D"nil">receiver_account_id =3D NULL</span><br>
          <span class=3D"set">beneficiary_id&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=
nbsp;=3D "B0234"</span><br><br>
          Money leaves the bank entirely.<br>
          Join beneficiaries -&gt; type &amp; country risk.<br>
          No customer record exists for external parties.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- JOIN RECIPES -->
<div class=3D"recipes" style=3D"margin-top:20px;padding-bottom:20px">
  <div class=3D"recipes-head">Join Recipes</div>
  <div class=3D"recipes-grid">

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">01 - Transactions -&gt; Customers</div>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d"><code>customer_id</code> is denormalised into =
every row - single-key, zero chaining.</div>
      <div class=3D"code"><span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>.merge(
  <span class=3D"ct">customers</span>, <span class=3D"ck">on</span>=3D<span=
 class=3D"cs">"customer_id"</span>
)</div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">02 - Transactions -&gt; Accounts (sender)</div=
>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d">Brings in balance, open_days, and all risk att=
ributes via one join.</div>
      <div class=3D"code"><span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>.merge(
  <span class=3D"ct">accounts</span>,
  <span class=3D"ck">left_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"sender_account_id=
"</span>,
  <span class=3D"ck">right_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"account_id"</spa=
n>
)</div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">03 - Transactions -&gt; Accounts (receiver)</d=
iv>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d">Internal transfers only. Always <code>how=3D"l=
eft"</code> - this FK is nullable.</div>
      <div class=3D"code"><span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>.merge(
  <span class=3D"ct">accounts</span>,
  <span class=3D"ck">left_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"receiver_account_=
id"</span>,
  <span class=3D"ck">right_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"account_id"</spa=
n>,
  <span class=3D"ck">how</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"left"</span>
)</div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">04 - Transactions -&gt; Devices</div>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d">Get device risk signals: rooted, VPN, emulator=
, OS type.</div>
      <div class=3D"code"><span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>.merge(
  <span class=3D"ct">devices</span>, <span class=3D"ck">on</span>=3D<span c=
lass=3D"cs">"device_id"</span>
)</div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">05 - Transactions -&gt; Beneficiaries</div>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d">External transfers only. Filter first to avoid=
 NaN rows.</div>
      <div class=3D"code"><span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>[
  <span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>[<span class=3D"cs">"beneficiary_id=
"</span>].notna()
].merge(<span class=3D"ct">beneficiaries</span>, <span class=3D"ck">on</spa=
n>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"beneficiary_id"</span>)</div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">06 - Sender + Receiver (no column clash)</div>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d">Prefix both sides to avoid <code>col_x / col_y=
</code> naming collision.</div>
      <div class=3D"code">s =3D <span class=3D"ct">accounts</span>.add_pref=
ix(<span class=3D"cs">"sndr_"</span>)
r =3D <span class=3D"ct">accounts</span>.add_prefix(<span class=3D"cs">"rcv=
r_"</span>)
<span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>
  .merge(s, <span class=3D"ck">left_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"sender_=
account_id"</span>,
            <span class=3D"ck">right_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"sndr_a=
ccount_id"</span>)
  .merge(r, <span class=3D"ck">left_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"receive=
r_account_id"</span>,
            <span class=3D"ck">right_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"rcvr_a=
ccount_id"</span>,
            <span class=3D"ck">how</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"left"</span=
>)</div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">07 - Devices -&gt; Customers (indirect)</div>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d">No direct FK. Transactions is the bridge - alw=
ays route through it.</div>
      <div class=3D"code"><span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>
  .merge(<span class=3D"ct">devices</span>, <span class=3D"ck">on</span>=3D=
<span class=3D"cs">"device_id"</span>)
  .merge(<span class=3D"ct">customers</span>, <span class=3D"ck">on</span>=
=3D<span class=3D"cs">"customer_id"</span>)
  .query(<span class=3D"cs">"rooted_flag =3D=3D 1"</span>)</div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">08 - Beneficiaries -&gt; Customers (indirect)<=
/div>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d">Who sent money to crypto exchanges? Route thro=
ugh transactions.</div>
      <div class=3D"code"><span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>
  .merge(<span class=3D"ct">beneficiaries</span>, <span class=3D"ck">on</sp=
an>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"beneficiary_id"</span>)
  .merge(<span class=3D"ct">customers</span>, <span class=3D"ck">on</span>=
=3D<span class=3D"cs">"customer_id"</span>)
  .query(<span class=3D"cs">"beneficiary_type =3D=3D 'crypto'"</span>)</div=
>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">09 - Graph Edges FK Coverage</div>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d">graph_edges has three FK joins: transactions, =
accounts (source), and customers.</div>
      <div class=3D"code" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;overflow-x:hidden">=
<span class=3D"ct">graph_edges</span>
  .merge(
    <span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>[["transaction_id"]],
    <span class=3D"ck">on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"transaction_id"</spa=
n>
  )
  .merge(
    <span class=3D"ck">accounts</span>[["account_id"]],
    <span class=3D"ck">left_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"source_account_=
id"</span>,
    <span class=3D"ck">right_on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"account_id"</s=
pan>
  )
  .merge(
    <span class=3D"ck">customers</span>[["customer_id"]],
    <span class=3D"ck">on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"customer_id"</span>
  )</div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rcard">
      <div class=3D"rcard-h">10 - Customers to Transactions Schema</div>
      <div class=3D"rcard-d">Cardinality: one customer can have many transa=
ctions; each transaction maps to one customer.</div>
      <div class=3D"code" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;overflow-x:hidden">=
<span class=3D"cm">customers.customer_id (PK) 1 --- * transactions.customer=
_id (FK)</span>
<span class=3D"ct">customers</span>.merge(
  <span class=3D"ck">transactions</span>,
  <span class=3D"ck">on</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"customer_id"</span>,
  <span class=3D"ck">how</span>=3D<span class=3D"cs">"inner"</span>
)</div>
    </div>

  </div>
